## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, etc.)
- A text editor (e.g., **VI/Vim**, VS Code, Notepad++)
- Git (for version control)

### Running Locally

1. Clone or download this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd <project-folder>
   ```

2. Open any HTML file directly in your browser:
   ```bash
   # On Linux/macOS
   open abc.html
   open world.html

   # Or simply double-click the file in your file explorer
   ```

### Linking the CSS

To apply `new_change.css` styling to the HTML pages, add the following line inside the `<head>` tag of each HTML file:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="new_change.css">
```

---

## Version Control with Git

This project is managed with **Git**. Common commands to get started:

```bash
# Initialize a new repository
git init

# Check the status of your files
git status

# Stage files for commit
git add abc.html world.html new_change.css

# Commit your changes
git commit -m "Initial commit"

# Push to remote repository
git push origin main
```

